#!CDarkGreen 
#!N  #!Radconp Adding Control Points #!N #!EC #!N #!N Control points 
can be added to an area using one of four different 
methods: #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N o double-clicking 
directly in the area, #!N #!I30 #!N o using the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Add Control Points... #!EF dialog box, #!N #!I30 #!N o using 
the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Generate Waveforms #!EF dialog box, or #!N #!I30 #!N 
o copying and pasting control points from another area. #!N #!I0 
#!N #!EF #!N #!N #!N To add a new control point 
by double-clicking, place the cursor on the location where you want 
the new control point, then double-click. The values between control points 
are linearly interpolated by the Colormap. If a new point is 
added as the bottom- or top-most point on the line, the 
new line continues vertically from the new point to the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
min #!EF or  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   max #!EF value, respectively. When a new 
control point is added, its data value is displayed by default. 
#!N #!N To specify exact values for new control points, click 
on the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Add Control Points... #!EF option on the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Edit #!EF menu. The  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Add Control Points #!EF dialog box 
appears, as illustrated in  #!Ladctpts77,dxall367 f Figure 77  #!EL  . The  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Add Control Points... 
#!EF dialog allows you to specify values using two steppers. The 
"Data value" stepper allows you to specify a control point value 
between "min" and "max." The second stepper displayed in the dialog 
will reflect that area (Hue, Saturation, Value, or Opacity) is currently 
selected in the Colormap Editor. For example, if Saturation is the 
selected area, the dialog will display steppers for "Data value" and 
"Saturation value." The value for Hue, Saturation, Value, or Opacity can 
be a value between 0 and 1. Use the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Add 
#!EF button to add the control points to the selected area 
in the Colormap Editor. #!Cbrown #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*    #!Radctpts77 #!N Graphics omitted 
from Online Documentation. Please see the manual. #!N #!N Figure 77. 
Colormap's Add Control Points Dialog Box #!EF #!N #!EC #!N #!N 
